{"key":"processedPost-7223863","value":{"id":7223863,"first":7190557,"last":27730552,"when":1185417100,"utime":"07/26/07 05:31 AM","content":"Sometimes, especially with wood or straw substrates, you can cover the entire spot with a salt paste to kill the mold.  Remember, the green is the spores.  If you disturb them, they go airborne and spread everywhere. Cover an area about 1/2\"/1cm away from the edges of the green with your salt paste.  Use about a tablespoon of salt and a few drops of water. Make it the consistency of honey.<br />RR","title":"Re: 1st growboxes with cakes and casing. Beginning. PiCs","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}